DEVELOPMENT SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
    This section outlines the steps
    required to set up your development environment for contributing to
    the GAZES project. Follow these guidelines to ensure a smooth setup
    process.

INSTALLATION
    bun must be installed on your machine to proceed with
    project development. Here’s how based on your operating system:

	Linux/MacOS:
	  1. Open you terminal.
	  2. Execute: 
			 curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
	  3. Restart your terminal or source you profile script to
	     refresh PATH.

	Windows:
	  1. Open PowerShell as an administrator.
	  2. Execute:
	         $ irm bun.sh/install.ps1 | iex
	  3. Restart PowerShell after installation.

VERIFY INSTALLATION
    To check if bun was installed correctly:
	  - Open a new terminal or PowerShell window.
	  - Run:
	        bun --version
		If successful, you’ll see the bun version
	    printed to the console.

CLONE THE PROJECT
	Clone the project repository to your local machine using:
		$ git clone git@github.com:gazes-media/gazes.git

INSTALL DEPENDENCIES
    Navigate to the project directory and install dependencies:
		$ cd gazes
		$ bun instal

	This will install all necessary dependencies as listed in
	package.json
